<section class="row-fluid">
  <div class="span4 columns">
    <p>Setting up my work environment required the installation of a number of, what I refer to, as primary development tools:
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://www.apple.com/macosx/what-is/" title="Mac OS X" target="_blank">OS X Lion</a> 10.7.3 is Apple's desktop operating system for Macintosh computers.<sup id="fnref:1.2" class="footnote"><a href="/about#fn:1.2">[2]</a></sup></li>
      <li>Google <a href="https://www.google.com/chrome" title="Google Chrome" target="_blank">Chrome</a> is currently one of the best web browsers on the Internet.</li>
      <li><a href="https://developer.apple.com/xcode/" title="Apple Xcode" target="_blank">xCode</a> is Apple's powerful integrated development environment for creating great apps for Mac, iPhone, and iPad.</li>
      <li><a href="http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/" title="Homebrew" target="_blank">Homebrew</a> is a package management system that is the easiest and most flexible way to install the UNIX tools Apple didnâ€™t include with OS X.</li>
      <li><a href="http://www.iterm2.com/#/section/home" title="iTerm2" target="_blank">iterm2</a> is a replacement for Terminal, the command line interface for Mac OS X.</li>
      <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z_shell" title="Z Shell" target="_blank">Zsh</a> is a Unix shell that can be used as an interactive login shell and as a powerful command interpreter for shell scripting.</li>
      <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wget" title="Wget" target="_blank">Wget</a> is a computer program that retrieves content from web servers.</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh" title="Oh-my-zsh" target="_blank">Oh-my-zsh</a> is a community-driven framework for managing your zsh configuration.</li>
      <li><a href="http://www.postgresql.org/" title="PostgreSQL" target="_blank">PostgreSQL</a> is an object-relational database management system used to store the data created by this website.</li>
      <li><a href="http://macromates.com/" title="Textmate" target="_blank">Textmate</a> is a general-purpose text editor used to create the documents used in the making of this website.</li>
      <li><a href="http://growl.info/" title="Growl" target="_blank">Growl</a> is a global notification system used to send notifications about recent changes to applications.</li>
      <li><a href="http://git-scm.com/" title="Git" target="_blank">Git</a> is a distributed version control system used to manage changes made to documents.</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/" title="Github" target="_blank">Github</a> is a web-based hosting service for software development projects that uses the Git revision control system.</li>
      <li><a href="http://www.heroku.com/" title="Heroku" target="_blank">Heroku</a> is a cloud application platform used to host this website in production.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>With the primary tools installed, I am almost ready to begin building a website.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="span4 columns">
    <p>The Book of Jack was built with Ruby on Rails, and before I could get started, I had to create the Ruby environment by installing the following secondary tools.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://beginrescueend.com/">RVM</a> is a command-line tool which allows you to easily install, manage, and work with multiple ruby environments from interpreters to sets of gems.</li>
      <li><a href="http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/">Ruby</a> is a dynamic, open source programming language with a focus on simplicity and productivity. It has an elegant syntax that is natural to read and easy to write.</li>
      <li><a href="http://rubygems.org/">Rubygems</a> is a package manager for the Ruby programming language that provides a standard format for distributing Ruby programs and libraries (in a self-contained format called a "gem"), a tool designed to easily manage the installation of gems, and a server for distributing them.</li>
      <li><a href="rubyonrails">Rails</a> is an open source full-stack web application framework for the Ruby programming language.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="span4 columns">
    <p>Next up, is to initiate a new rails app and set up the rails environment by installing specific rubygems, which is a highly customizable process, no two websites have the same requirements.</p>
    <p>This process will b commented on in a future article.</p>
    <p>Finally, the website needs to be deployed, which I have not yet begun. A future article on this process will also be forthcoming.</p>
    <p>As you can see, getting a website up and running can be a daunting process and has required a tremendous amount of time and effort. It's not for the faint of heart, that's for sure!</p>
  </div>
</section>

